name: Queen Anne Oasis
description:
New to HomeAway - over 100 five-star reviews from another vacation rental - Can send upon request.

******************

Large groups will rest easy at this newly renovated 5-bedroom luxury home with a guest suite. My home is centrally located in one of Seattle’s most charming and desirable neighborhoods. Minutes from all cruise terminals. Walk along quaint, tree-lined streets to restaurants and shopping on Queen Anne Avenue, or catch the bus a block away for a quick 10-minute ride to the famous Seattle Center and downtown. Afterward, enjoy dinner or a glass of wine on the beautiful fenced-in outdoor patio or soak in the warm swim spa.

You’re within walking distance of shops and restaurants on Queen Anne Avenue. A quick drive brings you closer to South Lake Union and Ballard, and only 2 miles from Lake Union, you can rent a kayak or paddleboard and head out onto the waters.

Cruise terminals are a quick Uber ride away!

INSIDE THE HOUSE

This newly renovated house includes the main house and a private guest suite. A total of five bedrooms, four bathrooms, two kitchens, and amenities that will give you and your guests a total five-star stay.

Inside, an open-concept living area shares space with the kitchen and dining rooms. Hardwood floors and classic furnishings characterize this home, with large flat-screens in most of the rooms.

The bedroom has a large king bed and patio access. If you can’t bear to leave work behind completely, you’ll appreciate the desk and chair that share the spacious room. An en-suite bathroom has a walk-in shower and single vanity.

Outside, the unit shares a patio with the adjoining unit. Sit out with a glass of wine while the sun sets over the Seattle skyline and soak away the day! The 14' heated swim spa provides an aquatic workout. owels along with kid and adult robes for everyone.


OUR LOCATION

The Queen Anne neighborhood is a historic part of Seattle, with gracious mansions sitting side by side with vibrant shops and trendy restaurants – like Crow, which serves new American fare in hip digs, and Canlis, a historic lake view fine dining establishment.

From my home, you can walk to Seattle Pacific University and the Interlay Golf Course, both less than a mile away. If you’re a water lover, head over to Lake Union, two miles away, and rent a kayak or a paddleboard for the day. If you're not into getting into the car, catch one of three bus lines that run along 10th Ave West outside the door - taking you downtown, Seattle Science Center, and more.

Come in June, when Fremont hosts the Solstice Festival, or live it up at Oktoberfest in the fall. Whenever you come, Seattle will welcome you with open arms!

itemListElement.name: Fun & Private Photoshoot in Pike Place Market

name: Fun & Private Photoshoot in Pike Place Market
description: The photoshoot will begin in one of Seattle’s most popular draws, the Pike Place Market. Familiar with the famous gum wall and Rachel the pig? Those are all popular sights you will see right here in Seattle. Experience the real Sleepless In Seattle with all the beauty that the city has to offer.

itemListElement.name: Enjoy A Photo Session at Seattle's Gas Works Park

name: Enjoy A Photo Session at Seattle's Gas Works Park
description: The Gas Work Park is a 19.1 acre public park located in the rainy state of Seattle, and is strategically located on the north shore of Lake Union just at the southern part of the Wallingford neighborhood. The park is now home to various pieces of old plantation ruins, and some hve been reconditioned and renovated for use.

itemListElement.name: The Original Paint Nite Seattle by Yaymaker

name: The Original Paint Nite Seattle by Yaymaker
description:
Yaymaker is here to unleash your creative juices. We’re invading bars and restaurants in Seattle with everything you’ll need to create a one-of-a-kind painting or art piece. We’ll guide you and your group through a lively experience of creativity, drinking, and laughing until your cheeks hurt. Just remember: It’s gonna be a blast even if you’re not an artist!

Our events aren’t classes—they’re parties, so preparation is easy! The canvas, paint, brushes, and all other supplies are provided for you at your event, so there is no need to bring any supplies with you (unless you are feeling extra creative).

Paint Nite events are partnered with local restaurants and bars. After purchase, visit Yaymaker's website and choose your desired event. At the checkout page, simply enter your voucher code listed on your TripAdvisor confirmation email. Any remaining amount due is the experience fee for your event.

name: Boeing Tours From Downtown Seattle
description: Your Tour Guide will share with you information on the History of Boeing and how the company has impacted the Pacific Northwest and the world with their innovation and technology. You will also learn about Seattle throughout the duration of the drive back to Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Ghost Tour of Pioneer Square and Pike Place Market

name: Ghost Tour of Pioneer Square and Pike Place Market
description:
We'll meet in the heart of Pioneer Square - the oldest neighborhood in Seattle. We'll go inside two haunted locations - of which one of them is part of the famous Seattle Underground! We will go to more than 10 locations in Pioneer Square, Downtown Seattle and the Pike Public Market area. 

Guests will hear over 10 stories of murder, mayhem, betrayal, disease and corruption - a story at each location. These stories are the reason for the restless spirits of Seattle. 

We will also explain how the ghosts can be experienced by guests at each location. We'll finish the tour at Kells Irish Pub, with yet another ghost story there as well. If there are under-age guests on the tour, we'll tell the story outside the pub, and if all guests are over 21, we'll tell the last story inside.

itemListElement.name: Food, Coffee and Wacky History in Seattle

name: Food, Coffee and Wacky History in Seattle
description:
A 2-hour journey of deliciousness, with stories of Seattle's crazy, dark and wacky history, and a total of 9 different food locations, and 12 tasting samples of fresh, local cuisine. You'll leave full! We are going to taste:

- savory (meat) pastries - at PIROSHKY PIROSKY
- sweet pastries - at PIROSHKY PIROSHKY
- salmon burgers - at RUB WITH LOVA SHACK
- crab cakes - at ETTA'S
- clam chowder - at PIKE PLACE CHOWDER
- cheddar mac'n'cheese (Oprah's favorite!) - at BEECHER'S
- cheese - at BEECHER'S
- coffee - at JOE'S IN SEATTLE
- probiotic yogurt - at ELLENOS REAL YOGURT
- donuts - at DAILY DOZEN DONUTS
- chocolate fudge - at ROCKY MOUNTAIN IN SEATTLE

name: Scandals History Tour at 2:30pm
description:
We will walk, take photos, and take in the beauty of the Pioneer Square neighborhood, while guests will hear fascinating stories of the rough, early days of Seattle: murder, mayhem, betrayal, corruption, administrative incompetence, prostitution, gambling and suicide, at each location. 

We also talk about the beautiful architecture left behind. We will teach guests the about rich history of the beautiful Pioneer Square, but we also want to show guests off-the-beaten-path places in the neighborhood. 

It will be a leisurely walk through the streets of the neighborhood for an hour, with about 15 stops (one to two blocks apart, between the stops), and we’ll have short (approximately 5-minute long), interactive and fascinating stories at each stop. I will encourage questions and comments from my participants, to make the tour interactive. This tour will be approximately two thirds of a mile walk (with may stops and stories in between).

itemListElement.name: Skip the Line: Daily Admission at Woodland Park Zoo Ticket

name: Skip the Line: Daily Admission at Woodland Park Zoo Ticket
description:
A short distance from downtown Seattle, Woodland Park Zoo is an urban oasis that sparks delight, discovery, and unforgettable memories in a botanical setting that connects visitors with nature to learn, care and act on behalf of wildlife. 

Explore 92-acres teeming with tigers, penguins, gorillas and 300+ animal species living in spacious, naturalistic settings. Be inspired and discover what action you can take to help save wildlife.

review.name: Nice place spend half a day
review.reviewBody: Really nice zoo with lots of open spaces and different animals grouped by location.  Got a bus to the zoo as it's around 20 mins ride Outside Seattle.

review.name: Fabulous for vecay day!
review.reviewBody: The animals we seen were so amazing & we took lots of pictures! So much to see in every direction... Just fabulous for a vacation day... Prepare for comfortable shoes &  a whole day cuz we only had 4 hours & missed so much to see.

review.name: Brown Bears!
review.reviewBody: We love zoos and go in many cities that we visit.  We saw many cool animals here.  My favorite was getting to see brown bears really up close.  Fern and Juniper were swimming all the way up to the glass.  So playful and fun.

review.name: Worst zoo in America! Do not come here!
review.reviewBody: If you want to come look at the trees and see a few birds, by all means come here. If you want to see NO OTHER ANIMALS by all means come here. Not joking, 95% of the enclosures are empty. No they’re not sleeping. They are empty. You’ve been warned!

review.name: Beautiful zoo; Nice animal variety
review.reviewBody: This is a beautiful zoo. If you see everything, including stopping for lunch, it takes about 2.5 hours to go through. Currently, the zoo is undergoing some expansion/renovation, so there are some paths and enclosures that may not be accessible. The zoo offers animals lots of space and beautiful, natural enclosures that are clean and well maintained. The animals looked healthy and well cared for. The zoo is divided into different sections, and offer a lot of animals and birds. There are plenty of benches where one can stop and watch them. There is a carousel on site (extra charge), three different opportunities for animal feedings (extra charge), and a food court. NOTE: You are allowed to take your own food/drinks inside, and there are plenty of picnic tables and grassy areas to eat at. This was a pleasant way to spend the day. NOTE: Parking rates vary, and are credit card only.

review.name: Great zoo
review.reviewBody: This zoo was really enjoyable to walk around. They had a lot of animals and many of them had roomy enclosures that weren’t just stone walls. I really enjoyed seeing the red panda, the lions, the rhino, the bird/rainforest enclosure. Also, this zoo was huge! Walked around 3 hours and still didn’t see everything.

review.name: Fall was great.
review.reviewBody:
Even for late fall the staff was wonderful and 
helpful, plus the wild life.

They had the lights at the woodland park zoo up and they were getting ready for after  
Veterans day.

Have taken my family there for 10 years or so and as a Canadian the price was great.

Most Canadians think because our dalloar being so weak thats it way more expensive, but in reality the cost to do this is cheaper in Woodland park zoo than the zoo in Abbotsford in BC.

I costed, 7 adults cost myself $107 USD converted was $137 CND. Thats not bad at all.

review.name: Fun day at the zoo
review.reviewBody: Nice walkable zoo. Like at any zoo, some animal exhibits, others were closed.  But overall a great experience.  Easily accessible by bus from downtown.

review.name: A fun get-away place.
review.reviewBody: It was a nice get away “from our daily routine” for a day. We hadn’t been to the zoo for quite a few years and it was fun to get reacquainted with it and see the changes that were made. It looked like a great place for young families to stroll with their young children.

review.name: What a waste
review.reviewBody: Everything looked the same: overgrown and over-decorated. You couldn't see the animals. Will not return.

itemListElement.name: Six Women: A Seattle History Tour

name: Six Women: A Seattle History Tour
description:
A Native Princess, a Gay Icon, a Swindler, a Zealot, a Madame, and a Mayor!

My new tour follows in the steps of these six unique women whose paths overlapped in the Pioneer Square area over the last 200 years. Some of the women were inspirational and some despicable. Some were masters of their destinies, others were victims of fate. Stand where they once stood while hearing their stories!

review.name: Great perspective  of Seattle history
review.reviewBody: We do history and food tours in every city we visit.  This was a great one. Carter is so incredibly passionate and enthusiastic, and she's  done a great job selecting the women to spotlight. They represent a great cross-section of Seattle history. 100% encourage visitors to take this tour.

review.name: A fun walk through time
review.reviewBody: A fun walk through time, our guide gave us a personal connection to these influential women and how they shaped the history of the area. With all the fun facts it was like walking in their shoes and living the history. The quality of this tour makes me want to find a walking tour in every city I travel to.

review.name: Magnificent and Marvelous Tour
review.reviewBody: Our Guide, Carter, was so well informed and interesting.  You could tell she loved what she was doing.  One of the stops were in Smith's Union Bar.  This bar was featured in the new movie "Midway"......how exciting to know that we were in that very same bar.  Oh the history!    Will certainly recommend this tour and would go on it again!   Do not recommend for anyone under the age of 16 though.  Thanks Carter!

review.name: TAKE THIS TOUR!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I took a late afternoon tour of Chinatown/the red-light district during WWII with Carter. Carter's storytelling ability is truly a gift - she will keep you laughing, waiting for the next twist and turn in the fortunes of those who lived, or saw active duty, in Honlulu during WWII. One of my favorite walking tours ever. Don't miss it.

review.name: Bill
review.reviewBody: Tour was awesome.  Carter (the founder) was exceptional in her knowledge and enthusiasm.  I went back to Smith’s Union Bar (in Chinatown) after the tour to have a beer and take it all in. Just think, how many USS Arizona sailors had their last drink there?  I’m an avid lifelong WWII buff and former docent at a WWII museum and this tour made my trip.

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody: Highly recommend. Carter knew her stuff and had us laughing the whole time. See a new side of hawaii.

review.name: Super interesting tour that makes you blush!
review.reviewBody: We stepped back into time. Carter, our guide was amazing. She was so animated, well researched and engaging. We laughed, blushed and heard of the sailor life during WWII. Not for children!

review.name: Loved it!  History and (sex)
review.reviewBody:
This tour is one I can both respect and love. 

I can respect it in an academic level as Carter has researched and documented every one of her facts. 

I love this tour because it tells (true) naughty stories of what soldiers got up to during wartime. 

Every last bit of history we’re given is PG rated. We all know our ancestors weren’t puritans but that remains just a suspicion.  This walking tour is proof our grandparents were as young and as enamoured of sex as were, are or will be. 

Bravo, Carter

review.name: Entertaining from so many angles
review.reviewBody: Well firstly I would like to thank tour guide for her flexibility as I got the tour time wrong.  But arrangements were made and we were able to do the tour, which is a big tick. The tour went through Chinatown, Honolulu which to be honest is not the top end of town.  But the detail and entertainment the tour guide provided was excellent.  I learnt so much in such a short time frame.  The walking is not taxing and we were both able to manage it quite easily.  Just a tip,  you will need to pre-arrange a taxi pick up from the tour meeting point, as this is the only way home, apart from the bus.

review.name: Best walking tour in Honolulu!
review.reviewBody: This was so much fun. Carter was absolutely amazing. Funny, informative, extremely knowledgeable and a joy to spend the morning with. The history of this period was fascinating. Being a retired Navy man made it even more interesting. Do not miss this!!!

itemListElement.name: Seattle: Book A Local Host For Six Hours

name: Seattle: Book A Local Host For Six Hours
description: Book a local Seattleite for a personalised exploration of the city. Your local host will build the best experience for you based on your interests. Discover what it is like to see the city through the eyes of a local.

review.name: Newcomers introduction to Seattle neighborhoods
review.reviewBody: I had moved to the Key Peninsula (50 miles SW) approximately 6 months ago and had been up to Seattle 3-4 times for different reasons but wanted a walking tour/history/get my bearings of the city from a local. My 14 year old nephew was here on spring break and I wanted to introduce him to a major metropolitan city experience also. I was paired up with Wiley who had lived in Seattle for a couple years. He was very involved in theater and swing dancing. Fun, kind, engaging and chill guy. I gave him some background on my interests for me and my teenage nephew but really let him guide us thru the city. Thankfully it was a gorgeous, sunny day. Mid week,lots of tourists,activity. I have to say this would have been pretty miserable for 6 hours if it had been cold and raining! We actually cut the tour short because my nephew was exhausted and our feet were starting to ache. I was very happy with Wiley, our tour,activities,information, lunch choice and overall day. I don’t think it was a great value(good value) and I wish Wiley was a little more informative on the history of the city.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Private Half Day Tours with a Local, 100% Personalized

name: Seattle Private Half Day Tours with a Local, 100% Personalized
description:
Book a local Seattleite for a personalised exploration of the city. Your local host will build the best experience for you based on your interests. Discover what it is like to see the city through the eyes of a local.

Our handpicked hosts are culinary connoisseurs and history buffs, bakers and bankers, students and seniors. Like the people who travel with us, they have different backgrounds and interests – but they’re all so passionate about the place they call home, they choose to spend their free time sharing it with the like-minded travelers matched to them.

Your meeting place and time as well as your itinerary are flexible, so you can plan and experience with your host to meet your needs.

review.name: Lovely company for such a beautiful city!
review.reviewBody: Vladimir was amazing! He was informative and has a very kind nature about him. Note: There is no way this is a walking tour, so we went by car. This means he relies heavily on tips for this to be worth his while... And trust me, you'll love it! Thank you so much for showing me the beautiful city of Seattle!

review.name: Loved this experience!
review.reviewBody: Vladimir was absolutely wonderful! We had the best day, conversation and coffee. Vladimir was so welcoming and passionate about the city of Seattle and the best coffee this city has to offer! We would absolutely recommend this tour and specifically, Vladimir!

review.name: Great tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour! We got to visit some nice coffee shops and book stores along the way and also we found an amazing donut shop. Our tour guide was friendly and had a lot of information about the city.

review.name: Unprofessional
review.reviewBody: I got an email confirmation about a week before my scheduled tour.  It stated I should be receiving an email from my guide a couple days before my scheduled tour. I never got the follow up email so I messaged the night before to confirm. At 6AM the morning of my tour, I got a message explaining my tour had been canceled and there were no tours happening right now. This was the 1 splurge I made for my trip and was strung along for nothing; very unprofessional business!

review.name: The Perfect Balance of Tourism & Dinning
review.reviewBody: This was the perfect balance of a touristy sight seeing day and a relaxed food and drinking day with a fun companion named West Liberty! This was a private tour so we got in everything I wanted to see as well as take in an excellent lunch and a hip coffee shop. I cannot say enough how knowledgeable and flexible she was and West and provided me an A+ day!!!

review.name: Fun, insightful , easy-going tour of top Seattle sights
review.reviewBody: I was lucky enough to have Sheila as a tour guide. She contacted me ahead of time to  personalize the tour and also checked in with me before we started (day of) to see what I was still interested in visiting. We hit the spots I most wanted to see - Pioneer square, the International areas, the Public Market, the first Starbucks - and she also highlighted so many other things along the way. Sheila gave me great backstories about Seattle and it's many attractions. She also did her homework to accommodate my food sensitivities, which was very much appreciated. This tour was very much worth it's while, especially because of my great guide.

Vladimir was an excellent tour guide, showed us exactly what we needed to see in our limited time in Seattle.

review.name: Transportation & Tour Guide Seattle area with our own agenda
review.reviewBody: Nature Nuts Travel provided excellent service for our team members visiting from Japan.  They also arranged for a Japanese tour guide that was very helpful and enjoyable to be around.  We highly recommend their services and thank them for the attention to detail put into our daily agendas.

review.name: College Student Group from Florida
review.reviewBody: I am the travel agent that confirmed a small group of college students traveling to Seattle and Vancouver.  We were so fortunate to find the trip with Nature Nuts that allowed the group a four-hour sightseeing tour of Seattle upon their arrival which worked out perfectly as the hotel was not available for them to check in so early.  Michael Joyce went above and beyond in his service to the group.  The flight was late arriving into Seattle but Mr. Joyce waited for the group and did not subtract any time from their sightseeing venture.  Upon the return to Florida, the entire group said that the tour of Seattle with Mr. Joyce was one of their memorable experiences.  We would highly recommend this company for everyone, but especially if you have a smaller group.  We, as a travel agency, will retain their information and use their services whenever we have clients going to Seattle.  You will not go wrong reaching out to Nature Nuts for all of your transportation and tour needs.

review.name: Wonderful 5 hour excursion to Woodinville
review.reviewBody:
Michael from Nature Nuts took great care of my small garden group!  We had lunch, wine tasting and shopping in Woodinville, WA.  He gave us great recommendations, offered assistance and was so flexible with our itinerary.  
Thank You!
Allissa at Full Bloom Travel

itemListElement.name: Cascade View Sunrise Shared Balloon Ride

name: Cascade View Sunrise Shared Balloon Ride
description: Sail aboard a colorful, nine-story balloon as gentle breezes carry you over the spectacular Snohomish valley, sweeping just over tree tops, floating above a river or lake, or rising high above the earth for a picturesque view of the Northwest mountains and waterways. Relax with panoramic views of the Cascade and Olympic mountain ranges, including Mt. Baker and Mt. Rainier, the Seattle and Everett skylines, Puget Sound, and the beautiful farmlands of the valley. Voted "Best Balloon Ride" in 2010, 2011, and 2012 in KING 5’s “Best of Western Washington” contests, as well as Best Balloon Ride in KING 5’s 2009, 2013, 2014, and 2015 “Best Northwest Escapes” contests. Morning and Evening flight times available. Post flight celebration and commemorative Pendant for each Guest.

review.name: Awesome!
review.reviewBody: Bob and his crew were amazing at accommodating us and answering all of our questions in order to make this a memorable experience for the entire group! I definitely recommend Snohomish Balloon Ride!

review.name: Amazing Experience with Snohomish Balloon Rides
review.reviewBody:
Bottom Line:  This was an amazing experience, and we highly recommend to anyone!!

We arrived at the allotted time and place to sign our waivers.  The process was smooth, however our Balloonist, Bob wasn't- due to fog and and speed- whether we were going to make it up and out that day. We had paid ahead for a special, private flight for both of us, so he waited, and tested, and waited just to make sure that we didn't miss any opportunity to make it up there.  And then, at the last moment, we did!!

It was just the two of us and a three person crew, so the entire experience felt very personable and COVID- friendly.  My husband got to help with set up and we got great pictures of inside.the balloon as it was it was inflating! Bob told of of his decades of adventures in ballooning as well as the town of Snohomish as we shot up to tall heights, from which we could see Mount Ranier, Seattle, and the San Juan Islands, then back down slightly lower again for a scenic tour of Snohomish.

We finished with a champaign toast, and a story about the history of champaign and ballooning. 

We are a couple in our 40's, who have had to face a major health diagnosis, and we no longer fear going on the "big adventure."  You shouldn't either.  Carpe Diem!  Book the trip!  You never know when it might be your last..

review.name: Breathtaking Views
review.reviewBody: Getting to leViewsThankfullye history of air ballooning and helping prep the balloon for flight really makes you feel as if you're getting the most out of your experience and adventure. Thankfully Negative Nancy wasn't having a bad day!

review.name: 10000/10 recommended!!
review.reviewBody: This was the best morning ever. I couldn’t be happier with my experience!! Great staff, and an overall wonderful time. I will most definitely be back!

review.name: Awesome
review.reviewBody: Captain Bob and his team are a real treat. One of the best experiences I’ve had. They even top it off with a glass. Absolutely loved it.

review.name: Fantastic!
review.reviewBody: Great people and great ride!!! The balloon is very relaxing and fun. Bob is an awesome captain and is lots of fun to talk to, as is the rest of the crew! Super accommodating and kind.

review.name: Winthrop Ballon Festival
review.reviewBody:
My stepmom and I have been dreaming of the day we could fly together on a hot air balloon trip.  We finally fulfilled this with Snohomish Balloon in Winthrop WA on March 6th:) It was was so impressive to see the process on preparing the balloon for flight and the staff was friendly and made us feel at ease. We were both quite nervous about it since we weren't sure what to expect. 
    We climbed in the basket and were off floating above the world or at least it felt that way:). It was an amazing experience to see my home area from 0 to 4000 feet above the surface.  The weather and the views were so impressive and relaxing at the same time! Bob put us at ease with his knowledge and humor! We loved it! The experience was amazing and we appreciated the tight knit ballooning family that shares their passion and love for hot air ballooning! Snohomish Balloon Rides are definitely recommended! 
     Sincerely, Debbie Schrock

review.name: Gorgeous flight in beautiful Snohomish WA
review.reviewBody: I honestly can't say enough amazing things about these people and the flight. WOW. Fabulous day to fly, we highly recommend the sunrise flight, we got up about 6:20 am for this, and were well prepared to get rescheduled but it was perfect an off we went. The operator is fabulous, very experienced and lots of stories about ballooning. He also made us well aware of what landing might be like. We missed our first landing due to wind so we got 20 more mins of fun. Finally the wind cooperated and we landed in a really nice couple's back yard. Super nice people and my boyfriend got to assist in getting the balloon in the right spot for others to get out. Super adventurous, exciting, breath-taking views. This was a bucket list item for us but we are SO going to do it again. These folks are fabulous and the celebration mimosa at the end was the cherry on top. YOU HAVE TO DO THIS. You will not regret it, also no motion sickness and don't look down and you'll be fine. It was perfect, worth every penny!

name: Full-Day Private Seattle Tour, Snoqualmie Falls & Wine Tasting, up to 12 Guests
description:
If your group has just one day to see the best of Seattle, this private tour is for you! Spend the morning exploring Seattle's top city highlights including the Space Needle, Pike Place Market, the Chihuly Glass Museum, Kerry Park and Lake Union. In the afternoon, we'll escape the city to visit thundering Snoqualmie Falls and head up to Woodinville winery country for a premium tasting flight. 

-Customizable Private Guided Tour for up to 12 people
-Explore Seattle’s top attractions on foot—not just a drive-by for a blurry photo 
-Complimentary private transfer for your group between cruise ship, Seattle hotel, or Sea-Tac airport 
-Explore the Cascade foothills and feel the mist blowing off 268-foot high Snoqualmie Falls 
-End this memorable day with a premium wine tasting in an award-winning winery in Woodinville, valued at $15/person

name: Seattle to Vancouver Private Transfer: up to 12 Guests, Flat Rate
description: This is a simple charter transportation solution for small groups traveling from Seattle to Vancouver.  We can accommodate up to 12 passengers. With this stress-free one-way charter service, you direct the trip and we can depart at any time you need to!  Whether you're departing from downtown Seattle, Sea-Tac Airport, one of the cruise terminals or another spot in Seattle--it doesn't matter--we'll get you to Vancouver!  Please note that this service from Seattle to Vancouver is assumed to take a maximum of 5 hours to complete.  If you require additional time for sightseeing or other stops, or maybe your group will return from Vancouver on the same day, additional time will be charged at a rate of $89 per hour (incl. tax).

itemListElement.name: Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, nightlife, history and attitude!

name: Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, nightlife, history and attitude!
description:
Center of Seattle’s LGBTQ community for years, "the hill" is vibrant, inclusive and delights with small independent shops, booming nightlife and attitude. We will learn about it's history and visit one of Seattle’s oldest parks with great views of the Space Needle. Along the way, we will check out a few of Seattle’s best book stores, some great record shops, sample locally made ice cream and confections, enjoy the best espresso in the city (in my opinion!) and see some of the most famous bars and live music venues in the city. This is a great way to plan your weekend agenda while in town if nightlife is your thing! These are the places I take my friends and family when they visit, I'd like to share them with you!

With a max of 3 people, or 4 if you all know each other, this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places you won't find in most guidebooks. Come explore with a 30 year local!
